        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 1:32PM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 132 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Naples, or 18 miles south of New Boston, moving
northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Wake Village, Nash, Hooks, Redwater, Maud, Red Lick,
Leary, Douglassville, Marietta and Bryans Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
